720754f-a.title: Manhattan: Lafayette Street - White Street
720754f-a.text:
Lafayette Street, at the N.W. corner of White Street (left)
shoving a gasoline station under construction at that location.
This site was formerly occupied by three small buildings that
bore No's. 94 and 95, White Street and No. 90 Lafayette Street.
A notice of demolition appeared in the New York Times of
May 25, 1938.
June 12, 1938
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

724756f-a.title: Manhattan: White Street - Lafayette Street
724756f-a.text:
White Street, east from and across Lafavette, to axter Streets,
and showing proriinently Fire Engine No. 31 and Battalion No. 2 fire
house at the N.E. corner of Lafavette and White Streets. Note to
the rioht the connecting passageway between the Criminal Courts Bldg.

will be housed in the new Criminal Courts (and prison) Bldg. that is
to be constructed on the blocks to the eaat of the present Cririnal
Courts Bldg. The clearance for same is partiaily seen in the right
